        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains 1264 proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation).\nThe heparin sulfate proteoglycan, currently a potential association with synapses, is based on two proteomic studies. Synaptic glypican receptors are identified (see above).. Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
